<a name="heritage">

<h2 align="center">Belarusian Heritage</h2>

<h3>Visit the</a><a HREF="../heritage/heritage.html"> Belarusian Heritage Page </a><img
SRC="../../images/places/mir/Mi_castle1.jpg" width="270" hspace="20" vspace="10" BORDER="1"
align="left" alt="Mir" height="178"> </h3>

<p>This project encompasses information about the historical and culutural Heritage of the
Belarusian people. It includes sites on various subjects compiled by the &quot;Virtual
Guide&quot;-time and links to other sources. </p>

<p>Here you can <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;... start on a journey through beautiful and historically
significant Belarusian towns and cities, learn about the history of more than 30 small
towns and large cities, see pictures of historical monuments - ancient churches, castles
and ruins - and landscapes - ranging from the lakes in the <a href="../../nature1/natbrasl.html"> Braslau region</a> in the North,
the hills of <a href="../../nature1/nathil.html"> Navahradak</a> down to the <a href="../../nature1/natpals.htm">Palessie</a> swamps in the South. <br>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;... On this journey through our country you will also learn
about famous representatives of our country across different centuries. &nbsp; &nbsp;
&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;... moreover you can read about Belarusian architecture, traditional clothing,
crafts and more. </p>

